$$K_b = \frac{[\mathrm{NH_4^+}][\mathrm{OH^-}]}{[\mathrm{NH_3}]}$$
Setting up an ICE (Initial, Change, Equilibrium) table and the $K_b$ expression, find the hydroxide ion concentration at equilibrium:
$$
\begin{aligned}
K_b &= \frac{x^2}{0.100 - x} \\
x^2 &= (1.8 \times 10^{-5})(0.100 - x) \\
