x &\approx 1.34 \times 10^{-3} = [\mathrm{OH^-}]
\end{aligned}
$$
Now, find the pH and pOH of the solution:
$$
\begin{aligned}
pOH &= -\log[\mathrm{OH^-}] = -\log(1.34 \times 10^{-3}) \\
& = 2.88 \\
pH &= 14 - pOH = 14 - 2.88 = 11.12
\end{aligned}
$$
The pH of the $0.100 \mathrm{M}$ ammonia solution is $11.12$."}

