T_2 & =-20\,^{\circ}\mathrm{C} + 273.15 = 253.15 \, \mathrm{K}
\end{aligned}
$$
Charles's Law can be represented by the formula $\frac{V_1}{T_1} = \frac{V_2}{T_2}$, where $V_1$ and $T_1$ are the initial volume and temperature, and $V_2$ and $T_2$ are the final volume and temperature.

